				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You appear to understand correctly.<br /><br />If your program put the local copy of OAM in $0700-$07FF instead of $0200-$02FF, for example, it should write #$07 instead of #$02 to $4014. In general, it looks like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; lda #$00<br />&nbsp; sta $2003<br />&nbsp; lda #&gt;local_oam<br />&nbsp; sta $4014<br /></div><br />where local_oam is a pointer to the local copy of OAM, and &gt; is the operator that returns the high byte (also called bits 15-8, also called the page number) of an address.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
